      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed operating points. All predictions within ±15% of experimental mean; RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cpb-vr-002",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pressure-rise validation across pump operating curve",
      "description": "Predicted pump pressure rise compared against experimental data across the full operating curve. Agreement within 8% across all tested conditions, supporting model fidelity for flow field prediction."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cpb-vr-003",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "UQ propagation — Monte Carlo boundary condition sweep",
      "description": "Monte Carlo simulation (n=500) propagating inlet flow rate uncertainty (±5%) and blood viscosity variability (±12%) through the CFD model. Output NIH coefficient of variation reported as 9.3%. A screening sensitivity study was referenced in the UQ report narrative identifying rotational speed and impeller tip clearance as dominant contributors, though no structured sensitivity analysis record is formally linked in this package."
    }
  ],
