      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study demonstrating discretization error < 5% on QoI (NIH) at the operating points of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation performed on meshes of 2.1M, 5.8M, and 14.2M cells. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH at the worst-case operating point was 3.2%, satisfying the 5% acceptance criterion. The 5.8M cell mesh was selected for production runs as the optimal balance of accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; fluid properties and boundary conditions match CFD inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro tests conducted using porcine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 33±2%. Flow rates controlled to ±2% using calibrated Coriolis meters. Rotational speed verified via optical tachometer. All test conditions are documented in the experimental protocol and traceable to NIST-calibrated instruments. Boundary conditions applied in CFD are directly derived from measured test conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
