      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is directly used to compute the relative hemolysis index (RH) for the acceptance criterion RH < 1. Validation activities measured NIH under the same operating conditions as the COU. QoI relevance is confirmed."
