      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model were selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump CFD. Model form selection is documented with supporting references. Formal model form uncertainty assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs identified and values documented with sources; uncertain inputs characterized with probability distributions for UQ propagation.",
      "rationale": "All 13 model inputs identified in the input parameter table. Deterministic inputs (geometry, rotational speed) sourced from engineering drawings and test records. Uncertain inputs (inlet flow rate, blood viscosity, hematocrit) characterized with normal distributions based on experimental measurement uncertainty and published physiological ranges. Input uncertainty characterization documented in the UQ report. Monte Carlo propagation performed with n=500 samples; output NIH CV of 9.3% reported. A screening sensitivity study is described narratively in the UQ report, identifying rotational speed and tip clearance as the dominant contributors to NIH variance."
