    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping. Uncertainty quantification was performed and output uncertainty (NIH CV 9.3%) is within acceptable bounds. The UQ report references a screening sensitivity study identifying dominant input drivers; the assessment team considered this sufficient for MRL 2 decision-making. The RH < 1 criterion is satisfied at all 5 operating points under both nominal and uncertainty-propagated conditions. The credibility body of evidence is considered adequate to support the regulatory submission decision.",
